{"block1":"<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Acquiring knowledge about hair loss is the first thing to do when trying to solve&nbsp;this problem. Luckily, a number of techniques, methods and ideas exist for anyone whose hair loss weighs on them. A handful of these tips and options are laid out in this article.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Although it may be difficult, it is crucial that you stay away from hair styling products if you wish to avoid hair loss. Products like gel, mousse, and hair spray contain harsh chemicals that can damage your hair.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"\/images\/photo-of-aloe-vera.jpg\" class=\"img_left \" alt=\"photo of aloe vera\" style=\"float: left; padding: 8px; padding-left: 0;\" \/><\/h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Some people swear by the effectiveness of aloe vera when it comes to preventing hair loss, so you may want to try it. Before going to bed, gently rub Aloe Vera on your scalp. You scalp will be stimulated, and the mineral content in aloe vera can potentially strengthen your hair.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Consider using a remedy that is natural, such as black strap molasses. Drinking two teaspoons a day can work miracles on hair and even increase your energy. It is difficult to take by iitself,&nbsp;so try mixing it with peanut butter or coffee.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"\/images\/photo-of-different-hair-loss-food.jpg\" class=\"img_right \" alt=\"photo of different hair loss food\" style=\"float: right; padding: 8px; padding-right: 0;\" \/><\/h4>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Never brush or style your hair when wet. When your hair is wet, it is extremely vulnerable to becoming damaged, as it&nbsp;stretches, and can snap and break when brushed. Dry hair is much better suited to brush and style, so wait until shampooed hair has dried before you brush it.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Your diet is worth looking into if you are experiencing hair loss. An unhealthy diet is bad for your hair, with excess carbohydrates and junk food consumption being particularly deleterious for hair health. Try to eat foods that have a <a href=\"http:\/\/www.livestrong.com\/article\/293059-high-protein-diets-and-hair-loss\/\"  >lot of protein<\/a> and are low in fat. Fish, poultry and fresh vegetables will give your hair the vitamins that you need to have long-term health.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Doing your homework about the topic of hair loss is a sound first step in dealing with your personal circumstances. There may be some options that you don&#39;t yet know about. The tips offered are just a sample of what can be done to combat hair loss. Give them a try, and&nbsp;look for other ideas to&nbsp;<a href=\"http:\/\/hairgrowthreport.org\/hair-growth-information\/combat-hair-loss-and-even-regrow-hair-using-herbal-treatments\"  >help you with your hair loss<\/a>.<\/p>\r\n"}